-- Crude Extends Gains After Statoil Prepares for Shutdown
-- B y   J o h n   B u c k l e y
-- 2012-07-05T09:42:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-05/crude-extends-gains-after-statoil-prepares-for-shutdown.html
Oil extended gains in London after
 Statoil ASA (STL)  said it was preparing to shut down production on the
Norwegian continental shelf as a labor dispute escalates.  Brent crude for August settlement on the ICE Futures Europe
exchange in London rose as much as 2.5 percent to $102.25 a
barrel and was at $101.92 at 10:39 a.m.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Buckley at 
 johnbuckley@bloomberg.net  